<div><h3>SOC 220 - Special Topics in Sociology </h3>  <p><hr>This course addresses current or timely topics, that are in a pilot phase or that are known to be one time offerings.Â  Special Topics can vary from semester to semester.</p>

<p>FALL 2022 &amp; SPRING 2023 TOPIC:<em> SOCIOLOGY OF THE BODY</em></p>

<p>This course explores the history of the body in social thought and discourse. How does the body affect the production of knowledge and how is the body impacted by social structures such as medicine, law, the military, politics, education, and science? During the semester we will also examine trans and non-binary identities, as well as body modifications such as tattooing and plastic surgery.<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> varies<br><br></p></div>		</td>
